      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Small field, but intriguing race with a few who have been knocking on the door clashing with some who have impressed at the trials. Will side with one of the raced in ETON AFFAIR (2), who has finished second in two runs this time in and draws well. That experience and fitness could prove vital. RED RABBIT (8) is proving costly and was again supported last start when disappointing, but is better than that. Heavy ground would be a query but she's good enough to bounce back. NARILAO (4) has won a couple of recent trials, albeit ridden out, but could give a sight on speed. ADMIRE MERCURY (1) has been beaten similar margins at the two runs but will be better for them and this race drops away a bit, so he can sneak a top-four spot.",
